Oh yes! I remember way back when (I was a teen then <g>)
there were huge rumours about Jimmy Page being a satanist
and satanic messages if you played certain songs backwards. I
still remember my friends and I trying to play records backwards
to see if we could 'hear' anything exciting. And of course, we all
had crushes on Jimmy and Robert <g>.

Meghan

messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 9/24/02 12:55:00 PM, superdiva@... writes:

<< After she left, the pro-Simpsons mom and I

wondered about how that lady could be so anti-Simpson yet pro-LofR.

I'm still wondering. >>

Well Bart says "eat my shorts," but Frodo says sweet mushy things about his
uncle, his friends, duty, courage....

I really enjoyed the movie, but I'm sorry and curious about why they didn't
say that it was Frodo's birthday too, and his thirty-third, his coming of
age. They just talk about Bilbo's birthday, but the really cool thing about
that party was it was eleventy-leven for Bilbo AND 33rd for Frodo, right?

Oh well...


Sandra

messages.subject: Re: [AlwaysLearning] I didn't know Led Zeppelin was demonic!
messages.msgSnippet: The demonic rock group Led Zepplin?  oh pleeeeezz. BTW, thanks for the earlier posts on the Christian shunning of Harry and their embrace of  Bilbo.  A lady
messages.messageBody:
The "demonic rock group Led Zepplin?" oh pleeeeezz.

BTW, thanks for the earlier posts on the Christian shunning of Harry and
their embrace of Bilbo. A lady wandered into out unschoolers game club
the other day. She had some comments about a Simpsons Chess Set that
was being used. She didn't allow Simpsons to come into her house. To
which one of the other moms said, "Oh we watch the Simpsons every day.
It's always on from 6:00 to 7:00 and we always watch it." "Oh." The
anti-Simpsons lady later began talking about LofR and talked about how
her daughter had all the posters and they were collecting the figurines,
and got the DVD, etc. After she left, the pro-Simpsons mom and I
wondered about how that lady could be so anti-Simpson yet pro-LofR.
I'm still wondering.

~ Alicia
